'[Verse 1]\n[G]Christ the Lord is risen [D]today alle[G]luia\n[G]Sons of men and angels [D]say alle[G]luia\n[G]Raise your joys and tri[D]umphs high alle[G]luia\n[G]Sing ye heavens and [D]earth reply alle[G]luia\n\n[Verse 2]\n[G]Lives again our glorious [D]King alle[G]luia\n[G]Where O death is now thy [D]sting alle[G]luia\n[G]Once He died our souls to [D]save alle[G]luia\n[G]Where thy victory O [D]grave alle[G]luia\n\n[Verse 3]\n[G]Love''s redeeming work is [D]done alle[G]luia\n[G]Fought the fight the battle [D]won alle[G]luia\n[G]Death in vain forbids Him [D]rise alle[G]luia\n[G]Christ hath opened [D]paradise alle[G]luia',
'G', 0, 120, '4/4', 'Verse1, Verse2, Verse3', 1, TRUE),

(72, 'Up From The Grave He Arose', 'Robert Lowry', 'Robert Lowry', 'english',
'[Verse 1]\nLow in the grave He lay Jesus my Savior\nWaiting the coming day Jesus my Lord\n\n[Chorus]\nUp from the grave He arose\nWith a mighty triumph o''er His foes\nHe arose a victor from the dark domain\nAnd He lives forever with His saints to reign\nHe arose He arose hallelujah Christ arose\n\n[Verse 2]\nVainly they watch His bed Jesus my Savior\nVainly they seal the dead Jesus my Lord',
'[Verse 1]\n[G]Low in the grave He [D]lay Jesus my [G]Savior\n[G]Waiting the coming [D]day Jesus my [G]Lord\n\n[Chorus]\n[G]Up from the grave He a[C]rose\n[G]With a mighty triumph [D]o''er His foes\n[G]He arose a victor [C]from the dark do[G]main\n[G]And He lives forever [C]with His saints to [G]reign\n[G]He arose He [D]arose halle[G]lujah Christ a[D]rose [G]\n\n[Verse 2]\n[G]Vainly they watch His [D]bed Jesus my [G]Savior\n[G]Vainly they seal the [D]dead Jesus my [G]Lord',
